CSS Basics

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a language used to style HTML elements.
It controls the appearance of web pages, including colors, fonts, layout, and spacing.

HTML Document with Basic CSS:
HTML:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My First CSS Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: lightblue;
            color: white;
            font-size: 24px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
</body>
</html>

Explanation of CSS Code:

- body { ... }: Selects the <body> element of the HTML document.
- background-color: lightblue;: Sets the background color of the <body> to light blue.
- color: white;: Sets the text color of the <body> to white.
- font-size: 24px;: Sets the font size of the <body> to 24 pixels.